# Progress — 2026-05-21 (TURN)

## TURN relay (Metered)
- `ice_config.py`: STUN + TURN (UDP 80, TCP 80/443, TLS 443) for host + `GET /ice-config`
- Client fetches `/ice-config`; fallback embeds same servers
- SDP filter keeps `relay` candidates; logs offer/answer ICE counts on host
- Toolbar `#info-conn`: connection, ICE, relay/p2p path, DC, codec, FPS
- Input gated until `connectionState=connected` + ICE connected + DC open
- Host meta delayed until connection connected
- ICE gather timeout 15–20s on mobile for TURN candidates

## Safari / iPhone pass
- Host: delayed ICE-failed cleanup (12s Safari, 6s desktop) — avoids premature peer teardown → "DC closed"
- Host: H.264 tune (baseline, annex-B, repeat-headers), keyframe prime burst, SDP H264-first reorder
- Client: iOS DataChannel unordered, Baseline H264 codec prefs, dedicated MediaStream attach, play() retries
- Client: DC close status only when video not playing; visibility replay

## Image quality pass
- Bitrates: mobile 900k, balanced 3M, high 5M, ultra 7M
- Mobile capture uses LANCZOS resize
- Desktop video CSS uses `image-rendering: auto` (mobile keeps optimize-contrast)

## Verify on device
1. Restart `python host.py -v`
2. ngrok HTTPS → iPhone Safari, hard refresh
3. Host log: `negotiated=H264`, `h264_tune=True`, keyframe prime
4. Console: `negotiated codec H264`, video metadata non-zero
